<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; COMMUTERS' DAUGHTERS TO RIDE FREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In recognition of "Take Our Daughters to Work Day," Metrolink will allow the 
daughters of its rail commuters to ride along for free Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Metrolink officials said they will provide the free trips to encourage 
Metrolink riders to participate in the nationwide program, which was organized 
to give young women a look at adult workplaces. 
</P>
<P>
 In connection with the program, Metrolink will allow one daughter, 18 years 
old or younger, to ride the train for free Thursday when accompanied by a 
fare-paying adult. Metrolink carries about 18,000 passengers a day along five 
Southern California routes. 
</P>
