<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ERRORS HELP SADDLEBACK UPSET FIRST-PLACE OCC IN 
SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback scored two unearned runs in the first inning and went on to upset 
first-place Orange Coast, 2-1, in an Orange Empire Conference softball game 
Tuesday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first home loss for OCC (27-12-2, 14-4), which has a one game lead 
over Cypress with three left.The teams meet May 2 at Cypress in the final 
regular-season game. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback's Amy Bloom started the game with an infield hit. Deanna Pallo then 
reached on a throwing error as Bloom went to third. Pallo stole second. Bloom 
scored on a passed ball and Pallo scored on a wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
 OCC scored in the fourth on Stefanie Ritchey's single. The Pirates had two on 
in the seventh but failed to score. 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Kesterson (17-14) pitched a six-hitter for the victory for Saddleback 
(20-17, 8-10). Kristin Varagne (8-5) allowed two hits but took the loss for 
OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 In other conference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 4, Riverside 0 -- Christina Mazzurie and Judy Enami hit 
two-run homers for host Rancho Santiago (26-17, 12-6). Jocelyne Patrick (24-12) 
pitched a two-hitter with two strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons scored their four runs in the fifth. After a walk, Brenda Parks 
reached on a fielder's choice and scored on a Mazzurie's home run. Christine 
Culver doubled and Enami followed with a home run. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 3, Golden West 1 -- Kerry Moloney had three hits and drove in three 
runs as Cypress (38-14, 13-5) won its 10th consecutive game. It was the 299th 
victory for Cypress Coach Brad Pickler. He is 299-119 over eight seasons.  
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Lopez gave up five hits and an unearned run to improve to 18-8. Golden 
West is 10-23, 5-13. 
