<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is sponsoring a free forum Saturday to help potential first-time home 
buyers. The session will be held from 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. in the Community 
Meeting Center's Constitution Room, 11300 Stanford Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum is open to the public on a space-available basis, said Jennifer 
Mack, housing program coordinator with the city's Community Development 
Department. 
</P>
