 "There is a big demand for this type of information," Mack said. "We've 
already received 650 inquiries from people thinking about buying their first 
homes." 
</P>
<P>
 Mack said the forum will have experts who will discuss such things as 
governmental programs for financially helping first-time home buyers. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the first time the city has sponsored a forum such as this, but we're 
thinking of making it an annual event," Mack said.BILL BILLITER 
