WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; FBI INVESTIGATING DEFENSE CONTRACTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The FBI said Tuesday that it is investigating a Camarillo defense contractor 
suspected of misappropriating government funds. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Auer, supervisor in charge of the FBI's regional office, said agents 
served a search warrant Feb. 2 at Research Management Consultants Inc. for 
company documents.No charges have been filed and the investigation is 
continuing, he said. He declined to elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
 Janean Daniels, attorney for Research Management Consultants, said the FBI has 
also subpoenaed several employees, but they have not yet testified before a 
federal grand jury in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniels said the warrant asked for some of the company's financial records and 
agents seized boxes of documents. 
</P>
<P>
 "Obviously, we deny all allegations," Daniels said. 
</P>
<P>
 The company was founded in 1988 and is owned by Raydean Acevedo. The company 
has contracts with the Point Mugu Naval Air Weapons Station, Daniels said, as 
well as other government contracts to do environmental and engineering 
consulting. PEGGY Y. LEE 
