<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; HEARING TO STUDY RENAMING SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A public hearing is scheduled Thursday over a proposal to rename a Santa Paula 
elementary school after a longtime city leader and current school board 
trustee. 
</P>
<P>
 The Board of Trustees of the Santa Paula Elementary School District will hear 
testimony on whether to rename Glen City School after Trustee Joe Bravo, but 
the item is scheduled as an information-only matter, and no decision will be 
made. 
</P>
<P>
 Every elementary school in Santa Paula except Glen City is named after a 
prominent local citizen, all of whom are white. The city is 60% Latino, and the 
name issue, which some community members claim is racial, has divided many in 
the city of 25,000 people. 
</P>
<P>
 Two months ago, former Trustee Bob Borrego proposed renaming the campus after 
Bravo, the former mayor of Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 But others suggested the district would do better to honor Dorothy Pinkerton, 
who served as the Glen City School principal for more than 20 years until her 
retirement in 1974. 
</P>
<P>
 Pinkerton has said she would welcome the honor, but would rather see the 
school's name remain Glen City, a reference to what the city was called before 
it was named Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 The hearing is scheduled for 7 p.m. Thursday in the district office at 144 
Davis St. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
