<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County is applying for a federal grant to help preserve historic 
portions of Piru that were damaged in the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved, the $50,000 Community Development Block Grant would fund planning 
and engineering studies to preserve sections of the tiny community's downtown. 
</P>
<P>
 Several buildings in the business district were "yellow-tagged" after the 
earthquake, indicating that they were dangerous to enter. All are listed in the 
State of California Historical Resources Inventory, which makes them eligible 
for historical preservation funds, county officials said. 
</P>
