<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; ARTS PLAZA GETS $50,000 DONATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks Civic Arts Plaza endowment fund picked up a $50,000 donation 
Tuesday, boosting the campaign to $3.89 million. 
</P>
<P>
 George and Maureen Jones of Westlake Village became the newest members of the 
Founders Circle, a club of major donors with special ticket privileges. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is wonderful to be part of the cultural development of our community, and 
we are very pleased that such a unique opportunity is available to us," said 
George Jones, senior vice president of Prudential Securities in Westlake 
Village. 
</P>
<P>
 Corporate and individual donations have picked up now that the grand opening 
is six months away. Funds will be used to support the ongoing operation, events 
and programming of the Center for the Performing Arts. 
</P>
<P>
 "Support for this project is just overwhelming," civic arts spokeswoman Evy 
Wiborg said. "Everybody is really excited about it." FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
