<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOP-RANKED EL TORO SPIKES DANA HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the first time in weeks injury-riddled Dana Hills had its starting lineup 
intact, but the Dolphins were still no match for top-ranked El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers defeated Dana Hills, ranked sixth in Orange County, 15-2, 15-10, 
11-15, 15-4, in a South Coast League boys' volleyball match Tuesday at El Toro 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Mariano had 22 kills and two blocks and setter Todd Steinert had 47 
assists to lead El Toro (11-1, 7-0 in league). Doug Thompson added 10 kills and 
Chris Jacobson added nine kills and two blocks for the Chargers, who only 
stumbled in Game 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Hefty and Matt Clem each had two blocks, and the Dolphins (8-4, 4-3) 
tallied eight in the game to post a 15-11 victory. Jeremy Darner, who had a 
team-high 17 kills, and Neil Hewko, who had 12, also had four kills each in 
Game 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Darner missed four matches because of a blood clot in his arm and wasn't 
medically cleared to play until Tuesday, Dana Hills Coach Oz Simmons said. 
Setter Wes Tsai also returned for the first time after missing a week with the 
flu and Hewko returned after being out with a sprained thumb. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
