<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carrie Breedlove 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Bell-Jeff 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Softball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Breedlove, who has signed a letter of intent with Arizona 
State, has 95 strikeouts in 64 innings. She is 8-2 with a 0.66 earned-run 
average and is leading the team with a .436 batting average. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Bell-Jeff and Mary Star shared the Camino Real League title 
last season, and were undefeated in league play entering last week. But 
Breedlove took over, pitching a no-hitter and striking out eight to move the 
Guards into sole possession of first place with a 3-0 victory over Mary Star. 
Two days later, she allowed only one hit in five innings of an 11-0 victory 
over Serra. She had 19 strikeouts in 12 innings. 
