<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Court Young 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Harvard-Westlake 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: The setter has directed the Wolverines' offense to 
near-perfection, leading Harvard-Westlake to a 13-1 record and the No. 3 
ranking in Southern Section Division I. Young is considering attending UCLA, 
USC or Penn State. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: The 6-foot Young had excellent matches in the Wolverines' 
impressive four-game victories against powerful Loyola and Mira Costa. He had 
60 assists against the Cubs -- who were ranked first in Division I -- and 62 
against Mira Costa. "He takes control of the offense and makes it work," Coach 
Jess Quiroz said. "He's our quarterback, and a real team leader." 
</P>
