<P>
FOUR COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES ANNOUNCE PLANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four community college athletes, including three baseball players, have 
recently signed to attend four-year colleges. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Minici, an outfielder with Rancho Santiago, has signed with Long Beach 
State. Minici went to Irvine High. 
</P>
<P>
 Rob Crabtree, a right-handed pitcher from Cypress, signed with Cal State 
Northridge. Crabtree attended Savanna High. 
</P>
<P>
 Shawn Allbee, a left-hander from Golden West, signed with University of San 
Francisco. Allbee, from Edison High, pitched a no-hitter against Palomar last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Tamika Harold, a sophomore center from Cypress, has signed to play women's 
basketball at Fresno Pacific. Harold, from Long Beach Gethsemane Baptist High, 
is the third leading rebounder in Cypress history. 
</P>
