<HEADLINE>
<P>
COACHES PUNISHED FOR RECRUITING; PREP BASKETBALL: TWO FREMONT ASSISTANTS CUT 
OFF FROM THE SCHOOL, WHICH IS ALSO PUT ON PROBATION. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SHEPARD, TIMES PREP SPORTS EDITOR 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Fremont High boys' basketball assistant coaches must disassociate 
themselves from the team for allegedly recruiting players, the City Section 
Rules Committee said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 After 3 1/2 hours of testimony by Fremont administrators and members of the 
coaching staff, the nine-member committee deliberated for an hour before 
handing down one of its toughest punishments in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the program was put on a year's probation. Fremont has one of the 
top teams in the City Section, having reached the semifinals of the Division 
4-A playoffs last season. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee ruled that assistant Keith Young made illegal contact with Kenny 
Washington last summer while Washington was enrolled at Wilmington Banning 
High. Washington, a 6-foot-3 forward, transferred to Fremont last September but 
was declared ineligible by the City Section for an insufficient change in 
residency. He sat out his senior season. 
</P>
<P>
 Irv Robertson, another Fremont assistant, was cited for recruiting Johnny 
Williams. Williams, a 6-7 center, was dismissed from Woodland Hills Taft last 
November for disciplinary reasons. The district reassigned him to North 
Hollywood, but Robertson told Williams if he came to Fremont he would gain 
immediate eligibility. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, who is now attending North Hollywood High, also sat out his senior 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Young and Robertson denied any wrongdoing at Tuesday's meeting. Sam Sullivan, 
Fremont's coach the last 17 years, said he runs a clean program. 
</P>
<P>
 "Nobody at this school is doing any recruiting," Sullivan said. "I have never 
done any recruiting, and I make sure my assistants follow the rules." 
</P>
<P>
 Coaches are not allowed outside contact with athletes not enrolled in their 
schools, according to CIF rules. 
</P>
<P>
 Barbara Fiege, City Section commissioner, said she will inform Fremont 
Principal John Haydel to make sure Young and Robertson are no longer connected 
with the program. They are eligible to return July 1, 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 This is the second disciplinary action against Fremont's basketball program in 
the last three years. It was also put on probation for the 1991-92 season after 
a series of fights on the court the previous season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042794-0108 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 036199 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
