<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAUGH LINES; JOKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jay Leno, on Howard Stern surrounding himself with half-naked women: 
</P>
<P>
 "I just hope this campaign philosophy works better for Howard Stern than it 
did for Gary Hart." 
</P>
<P>
 David Letterman, on the dangers of caning: 
</P>
<P>
 "It also could cause the kid to have flashbacks if ever he goes into one of 
those Pier One Imports stores." 
</P>
<P>
 Among Dave's Top 10 questions that teen-agers asked President Clinton when he 
appeared on MTV: 
</P>
<P>
 10 -- "Will your health care plan cover a wicked hangover?" 
</P>
<P>
 9 -- "Can you make a law that they have to play more U2 videos?" 
</P>
<P>
 7 -- "How do you keep your thighs so pasty white?" 
</P>
<P>
 6 -- "Does Gennifer Flowers wear boxers or briefs?" 
</P>
<P>
 4 -- "Hey, like, what's with that Gore dude?" 
</P>
<P>
 3 -- "This 'United States' you keep mentioning -- is that, like, a band or 
something?" 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Club Watch: Comic Kevin Jordan on Victoria's Secret: 
</P>
<P>
 "They should put a keg of beer and a few rows of bleachers in that store." 
</P>
<P>
 If you're keeping score at home, says comic Argus Hamilton, Roseanne Arnold 
now claims to have been a battered housewife, an incest survivor, a prostitute 
and a multiple personality: 
</P>
<P>
 "When you consider all this, she sang the national anthem pretty well, after 
all." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Gags Gang at Funny Stuff comedy newsletter says the one question Dr. Jack 
Kevorkian never asks a patient is: 
</P>
<P>
 "Are you sure you put enough money in the parking meter?" 
</P>
<P>
 The gang also noted that after four centuries, Michelangelo's Sistine Chapel 
masterpiece, "The Last Judgment," has been completely cleaned and restored. 
When it was finished, art experts discovered one of the artist's lesser-known 
paintings hidden under the dirt: "Four Dogs Playing Poker." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Reader Martha Roy of Fullerton says that years ago, her sister worked in the 
toy department of a large general merchandise store: 
</P>
<P>
 A customer wanted a present for her grandson, and after a quick look around, 
she paused at a soda machine, asking if it was messy. My sister's greatest 
strength and worst liability in sales was her honesty, so she answered: "Yes 
ma'am, I'm afraid it is."  
</P>
<P>
 The customer next asked if the machine was also loud. My sister knew the sale 
was lost when she told the customer that some mothers had mentioned the noise. 
To my sister's surprise, however, the older woman said she would buy the 
machine.  
</P>
<P>
 Ringing up the purchase, my sister said: "You must really love your grandson." 
 
</P>
<P>
 Her customer smiled sweetly and replied: "No. I really hate my 
daughter-in-law."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
