<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAUGH LINES; YO, ROSEANNE! TIME TO SPANK THAT INNER CHILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE MILLER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES; Stephanie Miller is a comedian and 
talk-show host on KFI, AM-640. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 OK, so I think I've finally figured out the best thing about Tom and Roseanne 
Arnold. 
</P>
<P>
 No matter who you are, they make your relationship look really healthy. 
</P>
<P>
 Well, perhaps with the exception of that couple here in Los Angeles who 
reconciled after she cut off his testicles with a pair of scissors. Must be a 
variation on a theme of the "three strikes and you're out" bill. 
</P>
<P>
 But short of someone lopping off a body part (which, by the way, should be a 
teensy warning sign), how do you know if you're in a dysfunctional 
relationship?  
</P>
<P>
 Well, funny you should ask, because that's the subject of today's lesson. (Are 
you paying attention, Roseanne? You, in particular, will be tested on this 
later.) 
</P>
<P>
 Personally, I hate the New Age, psychobabble-type connotation of the term 
dysfunctional . I think Tom and Roseanne each ought to find their inner child 
and spank it. Hard. 
</P>
<P>
 But I mean that in a loving way. So out of love, I offer them, and you, this 
handy 10-tip guide: "How to Know If You're in a Dysfunctional Relationship." 
</P>
<P>
 1. When more than three of your multiple personalities hate your spouse. And 
one of them starts channeling Lorena Bobbitt on a regular basis. 
</P>
<P>
 2. When your husband wants something called "loose meat" on the menu at your 
diner, that's a good indication there may be some infidelity to deal with at 
some point. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonus tip: When your spouse refers to "my beautiful 24-year-old assistant" he 
always means "my sex slave-girlfriend, but I'm stupid enough to think no one 
knows it." 
</P>
<P>
 Extra bonus tip: When he asks you to marry a woman as a "joke," the joke's 
probably on you. 
</P>
<P>
 3. When your "disagreements" could be new events on "American Gladiators." 
</P>
<P>
 4. When she asks you to convert to her religion, and you look like Beaver 
Cleaver in a yarmulke. Or when he asks you to take his last name, and suddenly 
you realize that you're named after the pig on "Green Acres." 
</P>
<P>
 5. When your wife enjoys kissing Mariel Hemingway more than you. 
</P>
<P>
 6. When your husband's idea of your "marital duties" is getting him his own TV 
show. (Subtract extra points for multiple TV shows and really bad TV shows.) 
</P>
<P>
 7. When any of your dates include getting tattoos or dropping your pants in 
front of more that 70,000 people at a time. 
</P>
<P>
 8. When your spouse is making more than, oh, say $20 million a year off you, 
especially when some of that money comes from selling embarrassing personal 
information about you to the National Enquirer. 
</P>
<P>
 9. When your spouse has roughly the same amount of pharmaceuticals in him or 
her at any given time as Elvis -- or a medium-size Thrifty drug store. 
</P>
<P>
 10. When you begin to "recover" vague but horrific memories that your spouse 
made you embarrass yourself in front of the entire country by mud-wrestling on 
the cover of Vanity Fair, and made you sing the national anthem while you 
grabbed your crotch at a baseball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Well, kids, I hope you did well on our little quiz today. But if you didn't 
(and you know who you are), never fear. I just did it as a publicity stunt 
anyway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
