<HEADLINE>
<P>
'HOUSE OF HORROR' IN BRITAIN FOR SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Britain's "House of Horror," where police have exhumed nine female bodies, is 
being put up for sale, lawyers for accused serial killer Frederick West and his 
wife, Rosemary, said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 West, a 52-year-old builder, has been charged with the murder of nine young 
women whose remains were dug up by police from the yard, cellar and a bathroom 
wall at the house in a police operation that began in February. 
</P>
<P>
 He has also been charged with the murder of his first wife, Catherine, whose 
remains were found in a field near the village of Much Marcle, northwest of 
Gloucester. Rosemary West has also been charged with one of the murders. 
</P>
<P>
 Police on Tuesday began digging for bodies at a second home once occupied by 
West, also located in Gloucester. 
</P>
<P>
 They said they had no objection to the sale of the house at 25 Cromwell St., 
dubbed the "House of Horror" by British media. 
</P>
