<P>
NIXON STAMP EXPECTED TO BE ISSUED ON JAN. 9 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A commemorative stamp honoring Richard Nixon will be issued Jan. 9, 1995, if 
past U.S. Postal Service practices are continued as expected, a U.S. Postal 
Service spokeswoman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Postal Service practice has been to issue commemorative stamps of 
Presidents on their first birthday following their death, said Monica Hand. 
</P>
<P>
 Presidents are the only individuals selected for a stamp who are exempt from 
the Postal Service's customary 10-year wait following death, Hand said. 
</P>
