<P>
 California Settles With Prudential: The state, the last to hold out on 
settling with Prudential Securities Inc. over its limited-partnership fiasco, 
signed a final settlement.The terms were the same as those announced by the 
state Department of Corporations several weeks ago when it said an accord was 
imminent. Prudential will pay a $500,000 penalty to the state and reimburse it 
for its investigation costs. The brokerage will also have to report frequently 
to the state on compliance by its California branches. The Corporations 
Department urged Prudential partnership investors to call a toll-free hot line, 
(800) 589-4678, for information on reimbursement from a $330-million settlement 
fund Prudential has established. 
