<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; APARTMENT OWNERS CAN GET FREE TOILETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City apartment owners are eligible to receive free ultra-low-flush toilets to 
replace older, less efficient models under a new city program. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will deliver new toilets to apartment owners who replace at least 25 
old toilets.Apartment owners are responsible for installation. 
</P>
<P>
 In multifamily housing units, toilets can account for more than 40% of 
interior water use, city officials said. The new 1.6-gallon fixtures conserve 
up to five gallons per flush when compared to standard models. 
</P>
<P>
 "With rising water costs, conservation programs like this become Anaheim's 
most economical water supply source," said Mariann S. Long, Anaheim public 
utilities resource efficiency programs manager. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 5,200 toilets are available through the program. Old toilets will 
be recycled and crushed for roadbed material. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (800) 660-8028.MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
