<HEADLINE>
<P>
RICHARD NIXON: 1913-1994; CLOSED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Researched by LESLIE BERKMAN and AILEEN CHO / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some schools and offices in Orange County will be closed today and some events 
postponed in recognition of a national day of mourning for former President 
Richard Nixon. 
</P>
<P>
 FACILITIES CLOSED 
</P>
<P>
 Nationwide 
</P>
<P>
 * Federal offices are closed, except for U.S. District courthouses in Santa 
Ana and Los Angeles.Each judge will decide whether to hold court sessions, but 
the District Court clerk's office will remain open. 
</P>
<P>
 * U.S. Postal Service will suspend regular mail delivery and window service. 
</P>
<P>
 * New York Stock Exchange, American Stock Exchange and Nasdaq. 
</P>
<P>
 Regional 
</P>
<P>
 * Saddleback Community College and Irvine Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 * All 28 schools in the Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 * Yorba Linda city offices. 
</P>
<P>
 * Imperial Highway branch of Capital Bank in Yorba Linda will close at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 EVENTS CANCELED OR RESCHEDULED 
</P>
<P>
 * The Yorba Linda Planning Commission evening meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 * The South Coast Air Quality Management District evening meeting in Newport 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * West Little League games at the Valley View Sports Park in Yorba Linda. 
</P>
<P>
 * Yorba Linda city recreation classes. 
</P>
<P>
 Researched by LESLIE BERKMAN and AILEEN CHO / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
