<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLOSED FOR NIXON FUNERAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A national day of mourning has been declared today , the day of former 
President Richard Nixon's funeral.  
</P>
<P>
 * Federal offices: Closed. 
</P>
<P>
 * Federal courts: Courts in Los Angeles will remain open, with each District 
Court judge deciding whether to recess. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: No regular mail delivery today. Express mail and special delivery 
items will be delivered.  
</P>
<P>
 * Stock market: The New York Stock Exchange, the American Stock Exchange and 
the Nasdaq will be closed today. The Chicago Mercantile Exchange plans to close 
its stock index futures and options contracts today, but the Chicago Board of 
Trade plans a regular trading session. 
</P>
