VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: FOREST SHOOTING AREA TO CLOSE MAY 2-4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MYRON LEVIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kentucky Shooting Area off of Angeles Forest Highway in the Tujunga ranger 
district will be closed to the public from May 2 through May 4, U. S. Forest 
Service officials have announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The closure, to take effect at 4:30 p.m. on May 2, is needed so officials can 
conduct a site inventory that will be part of an environmental assessment. 
</P>
<P>
 Foresters said the horse shooting area near Wrightwood and "A Place to Shoot" 
on San Francisquito Canyon Road in the Saugus ranger district are recommended 
alternatives for those who want to shoot during the closure. 
</P>
<P>
 Those desiring more information on the closure or other alternative areas are 
asked to contact the Tujunga ranger station at (818) 899 1900 or Angeles forest 
headquarters at 574-5200. MYRON LEVIN 
