<P>
 Gish Biomedical Inc.: The Irvine medical products manufacturer reported a 28% 
decline in profit for its latest quarter to $297,600, or 10 cents a share, from 
$412,300, or 13 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier.Revenue for 
the company's third fiscal quarter, which ended March 31, increased 2% to $5.3 
million from $5.2 million. Year-to-date profit totaled $828,200, or 27 cents a 
share, down 38% from earnings of $1.3 million, or 40 cents a share, for the 
same period a year earlier. Nine-month sales rose 1% to $15.6 million from 
$15.4 million. Gish said earnings have been reduced by expanded research and 
development, reorganization of the company's distribution network and 
investment in facilities. 
